John Gavan Duffy1

M, #384273, b. 1844, d. March 1917

Last Edited=4 Dec 2010

John Gavan Duffy was born in 1844.1 He was the son of Hon. Sir Charles Gavan Duffy and Emily McLaughlin.2 He married Margaret Callan, daughter of Dr. G. B. Callan and Margaret Hughes.1 He died in March 1917.1

He was educated at Stonyhurst College, Blackburn, Lancashire, England.1 He was appointed Knight, Order of St. Gregory the Great (K.S.G.)1

Children of John Gavan Duffy and Margaret Callan

Charles Diarmaid Gavan Duffy1

M, #384276, b. 1886, d. 1964

Last Edited=4 Dec 2010

Charles Diarmaid Gavan Duffy was born in 1886.1 He was the son of John Gavan Duffy and Margaret Callan.2 He married Barbara Madden, daughter of Henry Madden.1 He died in 1964, without issue.1

He was educated at Xavier College, Melbourne, Victoria, Australia .1 He was a practising Solicitor.1 He fought in the First World War, with the Australian Imperial Forces.1 He lived at Camperdown, Victoria, Australia .1

John Leo Gavan Duffy1

M, #384279, b. 1890, d. 1925

Last Edited=4 Dec 2010

John Leo Gavan Duffy was born in 1890.1 He was the son of John Gavan Duffy and Margaret Callan.2 He married Ruth Madden, daughter of Henry Madden.1 He died in 1925, without issue.1

He was educated at Melbourne University, Melbourne, Victoria, Australia .1 He gained the rank of Lieutenant in the Australiam Imperial Forces Artillery.1 He fought in the First World War.1 He was a practising Solicitor.1 He lived at Camperdown, Victoria, Australia .1
